’s a lot written and drawn on a single page! Or maybe because my mind is very unsettled for the last few days! Who knows! \u003cbr /\u003e \u003cbr /\u003eNormally I feel very homey when I read graphic novels. That feeling was missing here! Still giving it a 3 just because I don’t want to be impolite as the author has undoubtedly worked very hard to come up with the writings as well as the drawings.","rating":3,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/16297867?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2482778776"},"likeCount":12,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.FK4McOuUIJsGUU2FUxLfwA":{"id":"kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.FK4McOuUIJsGUU2FUxLfwA","__typename":"Book"},"User:3803671":{"id":3803671,"__typename":"User","legacyId":3803671,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1339470651i/3803671._UX200_CR0,31,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":1640,"viewableName":"Ivonne Rovira","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/3803671-ivonne-rovira","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":176},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.uSucNzEBOeqf4neUQIbVwA":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.uSucNzEBOeqf4neUQIbVwA","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.FK4McOuUIJsGUU2FUxLfwA"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:3803671"},"recommendFor":"especially for those interested in the 1980s","updatedAt":1641530899559,"createdAt":1433032020000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1442932545000,"text":"For those who are too young to remember the 1980s, it was a decade of utterly foolish magical thinking about nuclear annihilation, an era in which governments in both the United States and the United Kingdom pretended that, with enough shovels — and a stiff upper lip — people could survive a nuclear blast. Cartoonist Raymond Briggs published this illustrated black comedy in 1982 at the height of Cold War brinkmanship and civilian terror. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eIn \u003ci\u003eWhen the Wind Blows\u003c/i\u003e, pensioners James and Hilda Bllloggs take the official declarations and a home county pamphlet to heart and build themselves a fallout shelter in the complete faith that “they” know what they’re talking about, with decisions intelligently made by “commuters” (computers). James makes certain that the household doors used to construct the shelter are at the precise recommended 60-degree angle so that that the “fallout” — the couple don’t really know what fallout is — will slide neatly down the side. The rest of their plans are about as useful. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eMr. and Mrs. Bloggs vaguely think that this last war will be an abbreviated rehash of World War II and the recommended Inner Core of Refuge an updated version of the air-raid shelter. They soon discover differently. The Beatrix Potter-style illustrations provide a satirical contrast to the Bloggs’ overly optimistic faith in the Powers That Be to know best. A wonderful satire of those mad years. ","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/3803671?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1294300530"},"likeCount":11,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.9X7yKGpoeFfNttu0E96aFQ":{"id":"kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.9X7yKGpoeFfNttu0E96aFQ","__typename":"Book"},"User:1873333":{"id":1873333,"__typename":"User","legacyId":1873333,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1262445471i/1873333.jpg","isAuthor":false,"tex